Zero-Shot Lead Source Classifier Evaluation Report

This report uses only what the code produced: the CSV file, the confusion matrix, the results text file, and the script itself.

Overall Accuracy

The zero‑shot classifier got 73 out of 100 texts correct. That is 73 percent accuracy. The baseline that always guesses the most common label (Email Campaign) gets only 20 percent right. So the model is 53 percentage points better than just guessing.

